summary: ENB based upon Akiro Undone, elements drawn from Obethfeldt and Unbleak with tweaking for personal preferences.
descriptionHtml:
REQUIRES ENB SERIES 0.113 by Boris Vorontsov.

ENB based upon Akiro Undone, elements drawn from Obethfeldt and Unbleak with tweaking for personal preferences.

INSTALLATION:

Simply copy contents into your /SKYRIM folder

Make sure you also have 0.113 ENB installed
http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0113.htm

Make sure you install Dark Dungeons for ENB
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/12454

Optional:
Download Realistic Lighting with customization (set to vanilla)  *PLEASE USE 3.4a FOR THE MOMENT* - This will make interiors much darker and more effected by sources such as fires for a homely feel, if you prefer it to be more lit up this won\'t work well for you.
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/7654


********************************************************************************

http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bKjOB7JF43k&feature=youtu.be


The aim was enhancement of vanilla lighting with deep colours, very dark nights and dungeons (much like CoT hardcore mode - do not use CoT with this you will not see a thing), and bright daytime, chromatic lens flares etc. without much cost to performance. Realistic with a subtle fantasy/cinematic element.

I used Realistic lighting with the vanilla setting, best to use this in conjunction for the best result.

There is no SSAO enabled, as this is designed to run on my now old computer at above 30fps constantly. It\'s pretty much the only ENB that runs like this on my PC that I have used.

The screenshots are slightly higher contrast than in reality, it\'s just the way they come out.

Q: TitArse is a ridiculous name, why?
A: It popped into my head and it stuck.

Q: What are your \'aged\' computer specs?
A: Q6600 @ 3.4, 4Gb 1000Mhz DDR2, HD4890 1GB

It is designed to run with 0.113 ENB by Vorontsov Boris.

Thanks go to Bethesda, Boris, Obethfelt and Akiro for the making of this ENB.

This ENB was built upon,
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/21967
and
http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/mods/18941
